stdout: Have you heard of this thing called telnet?
It can do some pretty cool stuff
Recently I tried making a simple server using a multithreaded socket, of course in Python!
Likely I'll take it down, so here is a demo of what I made.
I have many more diabolical plans and ideas for other things to make, things that are actually useful :) So stay tuned! Here we go!
Would you like to see pokemon?
The server closes automatically after some time, although there is a little bit (or a lot more a bit) of Pokemon to show!
The awesome part is that you can receive messages, and then respond based on the user content.
You could also save data / read data from a database, and integrate something like machine learning, user names, and even hook it up to a web interface.
I hope you enjoyed this little demo, and that you move forward and catch em' all!
